posts.raw_content:
Have a YouTube channel dedicated to providing step by step instructions on how to cook each meal with live chat support to help.  Let people choose their meals online with a variety of cuisine that meet dietary/religious/cultural  needs the week before from a menu of 50 dinner options and staples for lunch and breakfast.  
Imagine the health benefits of people eating REAL food.  How much weight would be lost and how much less money spent on health care? Imagine the improvement of self esteem knowing you are learning to provide healthy meals for your family and you were a part of making that happen; rather than perpetuating helplessness and victimhood.
My Dad would always yell at me as I stood in front of the refrigerator looking for something to eat, "Make a sandwich!" and I would respond, "I don't want a sandwich" and predictably the response was, "Then you aren't really hungry are you!"
And for those unwilling to put in minimal effort to feed themselves, they could always select MREs for their meal options the next week.  Hunger is one of the most basic motivators in life, it wouldn't have evolve over time if it weren't both effective and productive--Let them Cook!
